Stream.take(n) is the bounded counterpart to Stream.runCollect: it truncates the stream after n emissions and then terminates successfully. Combined with Stream.iterate (which seeds an infinite stream by repeatedly applying a function), it gives you a safe way to sample a prefix without ever materialising the tail.

