Sequential `catchAll` forces every fallback to wait for the previous one to fail. If `primary` hangs near its timeout, the whole chain pays that cost. `Effect.raceAll` fires all candidates at once and returns the first success, interrupting the losers. The typed error channel collapses to the common failure type across all arms.

