Effect.annotateLogs attaches key/value pairs to the logging context for the duration of the wrapped effect. The scoping is lexical: once the inner effect completes, the annotations are popped, so subsequent logs outside the block are unaffected. Nested annotations compose — inner keys merge on top of outer ones, with inner values winning on conflicts.

